      • addValueRenderer

        void addValueRenderer(@NonNull ValueRenderer<E> valueRenderer)

        Parameters:

      • setValueChooser

        void setValueChooser(@NonNull ValueChooser<E> valueChooser)
        Set the value chooser. A ValueChooser will generate CollectionActionType.Add_Existing type of CollectionChange.

        A ValueChooser or a ValueEditor or both must be set on a ValueCollectionEditor. Providing neither will trigger an error.

        Parameters:
        valueChooser - the value chooser.

      • setValueChooserDisplayHandler

        void setValueChooserDisplayHandler(@Nullable ValueChooserDisplayHandler<E> handler)
        Set the handler to receive notification when the user wishes to choose a different value.

        If a handler is not set, implementations will provide a default presentation of the chooser.

        Parameters:
        handler - the listener.
